column32:
The granule south bounding coordinate (currently -90) falls outside of the collection level bounding rectangle.

The collection level metadata lists -60 as the south bounding coordinate because all latitudes south of -60 degrees are populated with fill values (NaN). GES DISC should take one of the following actions:

1. Adjust the collection level south bounding coordinate to -90 to match the granule level metadata.

OR

2. Adjust the granule level south bounding coordinate to -60 to match the collection level metadata.

Adjusting either the collection OR granule south bounding coordinate will ensure that granules are not invalidated by the spatial extent of the parent collection. Collection-granule spatial relationships are described in UMM-G documentation.
